and"},"en":{"–1158":"–1158","1110–1159":"1110–1159","–1174":"–1174","1140–1227":"1140–1227","1144–1174":"1144–1174","1154–1235":"1154–1235","about 1140":"about 1140","from 1158 to 1159":"from 1158 to 1159","1154":"1154","1110":"1110","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","1227":"1227","1159":"1159","1158":"1158","1235":"1235","1144":"1144","Abt 1154":"about 1154","um 1134":"about 1134","about 1132":"about 1132",", , , Switzerland":"Switzerland","Jerusalem, Jerusalem, Israel":"Jerusalem, Jerusalem, Israel","Grandson, Waadt, Switzerland":"Grandson, Vaud, Switzerland","England":"England","La Sarraz, Vaud, Switzerland":"La Sarraz, Vaud, Switzerland","Grandson, Vaud, Switzerland":"Grandson, Vaud, Switzerland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Sarraz","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Arabic/Muslim Gholam, Mehrdad, Pejman, Ramin, Afshin, Ali, Bishara, Fardin, Firouzeh, Fouad, Goli, Jamal.  Jewish Doron, Reuven.  Indian Sangeeta, Madhav.","Arabic and Jewish (from North Africa, Iraq, and Syria): occupational name from Arabic <i>ṣarrāf</i> ‘treasurer, paymaster, money changer’.","Indian: variant of   Saraf  , a cognate of 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Sarafian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Armenian Osep, Ara, Aram, Armenag, Armenouhi, Dicran, Hagop, Karapet, Khatchik, Masis, Minas, Sarkis.","Armenian: patronymic from an occupational name for a money changer, from Arabic <i>ṣarrāf</i> (see   Sarraf  ). This form of the surname is found mainly in the US, Lebanon, and France; in Armenia it is spelled (transliterated) <b>Sarafyan</b>."]},{"name":"Saraf","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Kishore, Rahul, Raj, Shreekant, Alok, Amitabh, Anil, Anupama, Aparna, Arvind, Krishna, Neeraj.","Indian (Gujarat and Mumbai): Vania and Parsi name, from Gujarati <i>səraf</i> ‘money changer’, from Arabic <i>ṣarrāf</i>. There has been some confusion with Arabic <i>ṣarīf</i> ‘noble’, which has also been borrowed into Hindi and other modern Indian languages. Compare   Shroff  ."]}]},{"name":"Jordane","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Feminine form of   Jordan ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"la","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Grace’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Jordane de la Sarraz was born in La Sarraz, Vaud, Switzerland. She married Ebal de Grandson Seigneur de Grandson about 1132, in La Sarraz, Vaud, Switzerland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1158, in Grandson, Vaud, Switzerland."},"et":{"–1158":"–1158","1110–1159":"1110–1159","–1174":"–1174","1140–1227":"1140–1227","1144–1174":"1144–1174","1154–1235":"1154–1235","about 1140":"umbes 1140","from 1158 to 1159":"1158 kuni 1159","1154":"1154","1110":"1110","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","1227":"1227","1159":"1159","1158":"1158","1235":"1235","1144":"1144","Abt 1154":"umbes 1154","um 1134":"umbes 1134","about 1132":"umbes 1132",", , , Switzerland":"Šveits","Jerusalem, Jerusalem, Israel":"Jerusalem, Jerusalem, Iisrael","Grandson, Waadt, Switzerland":"Grandson, Vaud, Šveits","England":"England","La Sarraz, Vaud, Switzerland":"La Sarraz, Vaud, Šveits","Grandson, Vaud, Switzerland":"Grandson, Vaud, Šveits"},"fi":{"–1158":"–1158","1110–1159":"1110–1159","–1174":"–1174","1140–1227":"1140–1227","1144–1174":"1144–1174","1154–1235":"1154–1235","about 1140":"noin 1140","from 1158 to 1159":"vuodesta 1158 vuoteen 11